issue.title: Fixes #98 - Moved API & MapReduce classes to their own module.
issue.body:
Pull Request for #98

Organized packages in core module.  Created FluoFactory class so users
can create FluoClient or FluoAdmin from API using reflection.  Core now
generates test jar to allow other modules to use utility test classes.
Formatted Maven pom files to use two spaces.  Configuration class was
renamed to Environment.

body: I like the idea of having one Properties class.  We could call it FluoProperties and it would correspond to one config file.  While most properties would have defaults, we could have methods in FluoProperties to check if certain required properties are set when running a client, worker, oracle, etc.  This would insure that users set the required properties when necessary.

was working on making phrasecount example work again, and ran into the following w/ props which seemed redundant.

`FluoFactory.newAdmin(props).initialize(props)`

issue.title: Closes #121 - Combined properties classes into FluoConfiguration
issue.body:
Pull request for #121

Fluo Configuration extends Apache Commons Configuration. Created unit test and updated
implementation to use new configuration class.  Added methods to verify
if configuration is set properly for client, admin, worker & oracle.

issue.title: Update references in README to new properties file
issue.body: In #121, all properties files were consolidated into fluo.properites but this change was not reflected in the README.

issue.title: Yarn props are not consistent.
issue.body: The properties added for yarn are not really consistent w/ the current model. The yarn properties are in the connection props files. Also the yarn props do not have yarn in the property name.
